body:
OK - I've narrowed it down and I think I know what the problem is - 

```
    win.on("close",function() {
            try {
                console.log("closing") // this o
                if (win.isMaximized()) // this silently fails???
                  ... // so nothing else runs from here onwards
            } catch (e) {
                // but oddly, this doesn't run either???
                console.log("Error")
                console.log(e)
            }
        })
```

I suspect this relates to the errors you sometimes get if you reload a page/use app.quit() - you get errors to non-existant functions/callbacks which belong to 'win' (remote.getCurrentWindow() in this case)

What I've found is using

```
window.onbeforeunload = function() {
    // "win" is accessible in here just fine
    // just bear-in-mind this will run on reload as well as close
}
```

works OK tho
